GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
# Alternative name supported by @google/genai / AI Studio docs:
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash
# Optional: override listen port for local `npm run dev` if the server fallback in `src/server.ts` is wrong for you.
# Railway injects PORT automatically — do not define PORT on Railway.
# Optional (production): comma-separated origins allowed to call the API from a browser.
# Example: https://your-web-app.up.railway.app  (omit to allow any origin during dev)
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-frontend.up.railway.app
# Optional: OpenRouter or any OpenAI-compatible /v1/chat/completions API.
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...
# Or use the same key name many OpenAI-compatible clients expect:
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...
# OPENROUTER_MODEL=google/gemini-2.5-flash
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
#
# --- Railway (backend service variables; set in dashboard, not committed) ---
# PORT — injected by Railway (listen address *inside* the container). Browsers use https://<service>.up.railway.app with no port in the URL.
# GEMINI_API_KEY or OPENROUTER_* / OPENAI_* as above.
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS — set to your Flutter web public URL if you lock down CORS.
